 unchanged from the 3D case. The evolution of the 2D and 3D\ncases is qualitatively similar. However, quantitatively the nonlinear energy\ncascade and subsequent dissipation is significantly slower in the 2D case.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 9 Oct 2015 22:46:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 4 Dec 2016 15:26:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-06"}
